					Groundhog Power!
				</navigationLabel>
				<contentItems>
					<contentItem id="126">
						<title>
							
						</title>
						<text>
							Groundhogs gorge themselves on grass and flowers all summer to build up a lot of fat. As soon as it gets chilly, they retreat to underground burrows and sleep until it warms up again the next spring. While hibernating, their heart-rate can go as low as 5 beats per minute and their body temperature falls to just above the temperature inside the burrow.
						</text>
